issue.title: [Potential bug] No remote branches, no tags after 2.11.0.0 update on Windows
issue.body: Hi I just updated to v2.11.0.0 on Windows 11. The remote branches and the tags are not visible anymore in left pane. In one case, there's no remote branch at all, only the origin remote and it is empty: In another case, the origin remote shows the "top level" branches (`chore/`) under which more sub-branches should be visible, but there is none: This happened when I had just woke laptop up, fork was already running and it asked for update, so I cannot really say if the issue arose even before update. But fork was working fine before I quit the laptop the other day. Looking at local fork logs, I notice this error recurring when I switch to another repository tab or I hit fetch: ```log 2025-08-17 12:11:16.670 RefreshRepositoryData 2025-08-17 12:11:16.670 REDACTED RefreshRepositoryDataGitCommand Revisions, References 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 8 ms: bt_get_references 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 Cannot parse reference refs/stash 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 11 ms: bt_get_commits 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 REDACTED Repository data are equal. No Changes ``` I also tried re-starting fork, with no luck. This happens with repositories hosted both on BitBucket and GitHub. For reasons that I do not remember now, but due to some issue with BitBucket, at least on one of these repo the origin URL currently also contains the credentials, with a scheme like `https://REDACTED_USER_NAME:REDACTED_PW@bitbucket.org/REDACTED_REPO.git` But problem shows also with repos that have no password in origin URL: `https://REDACTED_USER_NAME:@bitbucket.org/REDACTED_REPO.git` Problem shows up also with a fork of videojs hosted on GitHub: ```log 2025-08-17 12:22:39.882 Loading video.js settings 2025-08-17 12:22:39.882 Saving settings 2025-08-17 12:22:39.882 RefreshRepositoryData 2025-08-17 12:22:39.882 video.js RefreshRepositoryDataGitCommand All 2025-08-17 12:22:39.882 Saving settings 2025-08-17 12:22:39.906 21 ms: bt_get_references 2025-08-17 12:22:39.906 2 ms: bt_get_committer_times 2025-08-17 12:22:39.906 Cannot parse reference refs/stash 2025-08-17 12:22:39.944 25 ms: bt_get_commits 2025-08-17 12:22:39.944 0 ms: GetUpstreamStatus 2025-08-17 12:22:39.945 Refresh 'video.js' data. Updated. 2025-08-17 12:22:39.945 RefreshRepositoryStatus 2025-08-17 12:22:40.478 Refresh 'video.js' status. Updated 0 files 2025-08-17 12:22:47.396 Saving settings 2025-08-17 12:22:47.412 WindowActivated 2025-08-17 12:22:47.412 Application Window Activated: skip (FetchWindow) 2025-08-17 12:22:48.802 RefreshRepositoryData 2025-08-17 12:22:48.802 video.js RefreshRepositoryDataGitCommand Revisions, References 2025-08-17 12:22:48.819 16 ms: bt_get_references 2025-08-17 12:22:48.819 Cannot parse reference refs/stash 2025-08-17 12:22:48.826 5 ms: bt_get_commits 2025-08-17 12:22:48.826 video.js Repository data are equal. This repo has not been opened for a while, and I can see that fork fetched the latest commits on `upstream/main`, so fetch in itself seems to be working.

issue.body: Hi I just updated to v2.11.0.0 on Windows 11. The remote branches and the tags are not visible anymore in left pane. In one case, there's no remote branch at all, only the origin remote and it is empty: In another case, the origin remote shows the "top level" branches (`chore/`) under which more sub-branches should be visible, but there is none: This happened when I had just woke laptop up, fork was already running and it asked for update, so I cannot really say if the issue arose even before update. But fork was working fine before I quit the laptop the other day. Looking at local fork logs, I notice this error recurring when I switch to another repository tab or I hit fetch: ```log 2025-08-17 12:11:16.670 RefreshRepositoryData 2025-08-17 12:11:16.670 REDACTED RefreshRepositoryDataGitCommand Revisions, References 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 8 ms: bt_get_references 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 Cannot parse reference refs/stash 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 11 ms: bt_get_commits 2025-08-17 12:11:16.679 REDACTED Repository data are equal.
